## Advanced Details → User Data

Paste:

```bash
#!/bin/bash

sudo apt update -y
sudo apt install apache2 -y

IP_ADDRESS=$(hostname -I | awk '{print $1}')
HOSTNAME=$(hostname)

cat <<EOF | sudo tee /var/www/html/index.html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Auto Scaling Demo Server</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Auto Scaling Demo Server</h1>
    <h2>Hostname: $HOSTNAME</h2>
    <h2>IP Address: $IP_ADDRESS</h2>
</body>
</html>
EOF

sudo systemctl start apache2
sudo systemctl enable apache2
```

Create Launch Template.

### Explanation

Every new EC2 instance created by Auto Scaling will automatically install Apache and create a webpage.

